<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Multi Section Web Page</title>

<style>

body{
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
margin:0;
padding:0;
background-color:#f2f2f2;
}

/* Header */

header{
background-color:#2c3e50;
color:white;
text-align:center;
padding:25px;
}

/* Navigation Bar */

nav{
background-color:#34495e;
padding:12px;
text-align:center;
}

nav a{
color:white;
text-decoration:none;
margin:20px;
font-size:18px;
font-weight:bold;
}

nav a:hover{
color:yellow;
}

/* Sections */

section{
padding:50px;
text-align:center;
}

/* Different background colors for sections */

#home{
background-color:#e8f6f3;
}

#about{
background-color:#fdebd0;
}

#services{
background-color:#ebdef0;
}

#contact{
background-color:#d6eaf8;
}

/* Footer */

footer{
background-color:#2c3e50;
color:white;
text-align:center;
padding:15px;
}

</style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
<h1>My Multi-Section Web Page</h1>
<p>A simple website using HTML and CSS</p>
</header>

<nav>
<a href="#home">Home</a>
<a href="#about">About</a>
<a href="#services">Services</a>
<a href="#contact">Contact</a>
</nav>

<section id="home">
<h2>Home</h2>
<p>Welcome to our website. This webpage shows how a basic multi-section layout can be created using HTML and CSS.</p>
</section>

<section id="about">
<h2>About</h2>
<p>This project is designed to demonstrate the structure of a simple website with multiple sections.</p>
</section>

<section id="services">
<h2>Services</h2>
<p>We provide web design, front-end development, and website maintenance services.</p>
</section>

<section id="contact">
<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>Email: example@email.com</p>
<p>Phone: 9876543210</p>
</section>

<footer>
<p>© 2026 Multi Section Web Page</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
